Hey there,

It's Eric from Firecrawl. Over the past few weeks we've been shipping a bun=
ch of improvements to search.

First off, search is now 5=C3=97 cheaper at 2 credits per 10 results.

We also added category filters ( https://docs.firecrawl.dev/features/search=
#search-categories ) so you can search specifically for GitHub repos, acade=
mic papers, PDFs, news,=C2=A0images=C2=A0 in addition to web results.

And we added some other useful stuff like time based search ( https://docs.=
firecrawl.dev/features/search#time-based-search ), localized queries ( http=
s://docs.firecrawl.dev/features/search#location-customization ), Coinbase x=
402 integration ( https://www.coinbase.com/developer-platform/discover/case=
-studies/firecrawl ), and more.

Check out the complete search docs here ( https://docs.firecrawl.dev/featur=
es/search#search-endpoint ) and stay tuned for more updates!

Best,
Eric
